img = X[851]
#img_grey = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
#img_grey.dtype = np.uint8
img.dtype = np.uint8
edged = cv2.Canny(img,100,200,apertureSize = 5, L2gradient = True)
cv2_imshow(edged)
# Finding Contours
contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(edged,cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
print("Number of Contours found = " + str(len(contours)))
# Draw all contours
# -1 signifies drawing all contours
img.dtype = np.float32
cv2.drawContours(img, contours, -1, (127, 255, 127), 2)
cv2_imshow(img)

Embossing Filter¶

In [ ]:
img  = X[3]
kernel_emboss_1 = np.array([[0,-1,-1], #botton left 
                            [1,0,-1],
                            [1,1,0]])
kernel_emboss_2 = np.array([[-1,-1,0],
                            [-1,0,1],
                             [0,1,1]]) #botting right 
kernel_emboss_3 = np.array([[1,1,0],
                            [1,0,-1],
                            [0,-1,-1]]) # top left

kernel_emboss_4 = np.array([[0,1,1],  # top right
                            [-1,0,1],
                            [-1,-1,0]])

# converting the image to grayscale
img_grey = cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

# applying the kernels to the grayscale image and adding the offset
output_1 = cv2.add(cv2.filter2D(img_grey, -1, kernel_emboss_1), 128)
output_2 = cv2.add(cv2.filter2D(img_grey, -1, kernel_emboss_2) , 128)
output_3 = cv2.add(cv2.filter2D(img_grey, -1, kernel_emboss_3) , 128)
output_4 = cv2.add(cv2.filter2D(img_grey, -1, kernel_emboss_4) , 128)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.subplot(321)
plt.imshow( img)
plt.subplot(322)
plt.imshow( output_1)
plt.subplot(323)
plt.imshow( output_2)
plt.subplot(324)
plt.imshow( output_3)
plt.subplot(325)
plt.imshow( output_4)

Supervised Learning Algorithms¶

SVM, DT, KNN with Vanilla CNN + Max Pooling

In [22]:
model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(32,(3,3),input_shape = x_train.shape[1:],activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.4))
model.add(Conv2D(64,(3,3),activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.6))
model.add(Conv2D(128,(3,3),activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.8))
model.add(Conv2D(128,(3,3),activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(4096,activation="relu"))
model.add(Dense(17,activation="softmax"))
model.compile(loss="categorical_crossentropy",optimizer="adam",metrics=['accuracy'])

np.random.seed(1000)

model = Sequential()

# 1st Convolutional Layer
model.add(Conv2D(filters=96, input_shape=(224,224,3), kernel_size=(11,11),
 strides=(4,4), padding='valid',activation="relu"))
# Pooling 
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=(2,2), padding='valid'))
# Batch Normalisation before passing it to the next layer
#model.add(BatchNormalization())

# 2nd Convolutional Layer
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(11,11), strides=(1,1), padding='valid',activation="relu"))
# Pooling
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=(2,2), padding='valid'))
# Batch Normalisation
#model.add(BatchNormalization())

# 3rd Convolutional Layer
model.add(Conv2D(filters=384, kernel_size=(3,3), strides=(1,1), padding='valid',activation='relu'))
# Batch Normalisation
#model.add(BatchNormalization())

# 4th Convolutional Layer
model.add(Conv2D(filters=384, kernel_size=(3,3), strides=(1,1), padding='valid',activation='relu'))
# Batch Normalisation
#model.add(BatchNormalization())

# 5th Convolutional Layer
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3,3), strides=(1,1), padding='valid',activation="relu"))
# Pooling
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=(2,2), padding='valid'))
# Batch Normalisation
#model.add(BatchNormalization())

# Passing it to a dense layer
model.add(Flatten())
# 1st Dense Layer
model.add(Dense(4096, input_shape=(224*224*3,),activation="relu"))
# Add Dropout to prevent overfitting
model.add(Dropout(0.4))

# Add Dropout

# Add Dropout

# Batch Normalisation

from keras.applications import VGG16
#Load the VGG model

# Freeze all the layers except for the last layer: 
for layer in vgg_conv.layers:
    layer.trainable = False
 
from keras import models
from keras import layers
from keras import optimizers
 
# Create the model
model = models.Sequential()
 
# Add the vgg convolutional base model
model.add(vgg_conv)

model.add(layers.Flatten())

model.add(layers.Dense(17, activation='softmax'))

In [ ]:
# window/layout 

win = tk.Tk()
win.title('Image Classifier GUI-Great Learning') # window title
####################################################
name = ttk.Label(win,text="step 1: File Name")
name.grid(row = 0, column = 0 , sticky = tk.W)
name_var = tk.StringVar()
name_entrybox = ttk.Entry(win, width = 16, textvariable = name_var)
name_entrybox.grid(row=0,column=1)
def Import_Data():
    global pred_image
    image_name = name_var.get()
    image_extension = re.findall("\..*",image_name)
    if image_extension == [".jpg"]:
        pred_image= plt.imread(image_name)
        confirm = "JPG Image Found"
    elif image_extension != [".jpg"]:
            confirm = "Upload JPG Image"
    else :
        confirm = "Check Image Extension"
    confirm_entrybox=ttk.Entry(win,width=25)
    confirm_entrybox.grid(row=0,column=3)
    confirm_entrybox.insert(1,str(confirm))
Import_Data_Button = ttk.Button(win,text="Import Data",command=Import_Data)
Import_Data_Button.grid(row=0,column=2)
##########################################################
img_class = ttk.Label(win,text = "Image Classifier")
img_class.grid(row=1,column = 0,sticky=tk.W)
##########################################################

def train():
    global pred_image
    pred_image = np.asarray(pred_image)
    pred = pred_image.reshape(-1,224,224,3)
    model = load_model("best_model.hdf5", compile = True)
    output = model.predict(pred)
    for i in range(17):
        if output[0,i] == 1:
            output_label= i
    confirm = str(output_label) 
    confirm_entrybox=ttk.Entry(win,width=25)
    confirm_entrybox.grid(row=2,column=3)
    confirm_entrybox.insert(1,str("Predicted Label is "+confirm))
train_Button = ttk.Button(win,text="Train classifier",command=train)
train_Button.grid(row=2,column=0)

win.mainloop()

PART 5 Stratergy to maintain and support AIML Image classifier after it is in production¶

Ans To detect changes in data distribution we can proceed by monitoring both the output and the input of the machine learning model. One key metric to monitor the outputs is the % of predicted labels

1 – monitor your data 2 – supervise data labeling

Since in real life models performance decay with time it is necessary to keep humans in the loop throughout production. Humans are essential to:

Validate prediction with low confidence Relabel data in order to retrain models
